data.description: If you yearn for the quiet of a rural setting, but appreciate the closeness of life’s necessities, such as shopping, pharmacies, banking, etc., this 3 bedroom, 2 bath block home may be just what you’ve been looking for. Tucked away in the Ocklawaha community of Woods & Lakes, the home sits on a fully fenced, one half acre parcel that is private and roomy. The interior has been freshly painted in neutral tones that work beautifully with the warm brown hues of the flooring and the calming natural light that filters throughout much of the home. The living room boasts a brick, wood-burning fireplace and is spacious enough for two seating areas. A favorite room in the house will most certainly be the Florida Room just off the dining area and kitchen. There are plenty of extras on the outside, too, including an RV port, 50-amp electrical outlet, 2 additional storage areas, and a wonderful screened porch overlooking an above ground pool and large deck for fun and entertainment. The roof was put on in 2019 and the AC was installed in 2013, but has a new capacitor.  SELLERS WILL OFFER CLOSING COST HELP AS NEEDED AND NEGOTIATED.
